Hi, I'm running it on Node 8.17.0 and everything is working fine. I know that minimum requirement are Node 10 and above, but due hardware limitations on my Project I can't run another version of Node and I guess some users has or will deal with this situation in the future. 

Due to Let's Encrypt ISRG Root X1 expiration, TLS does not work anymore on Node < 10 except if use Let's Encrypt isrgrootx1.pem root certification file. 

An solution that I use with another services like, https client and websocket client was use HTTPS Agent like below. 

import https from 'https'; 

const ISRGRootX1 = fs.readFileSync('./isrgrootx1.pem'); 

const agent = https.Agent({ ca: ISRGRootX1, cert: ISRGRootX1 }) 

const ftp = new Ftp({
  secureOptions: {
      agent: agent
  }
}) 

I don't know if will help. But it would be interesting for other users that want to use this awesome FTP package. Thank you all. 

Sorry about my english, this is not my native language. 

-----------
EDIT
-----------
Problem was solved trying add isrgroot1x.pem file (download at https://letsencrypt.org/certificates/) in secureOptions.ca and cert options, like:

const ftp = new Ftp({
  secureOptions: {
      ca: fs.readFileSync('./isrgrootx1.pem'),
      cert: fs.readFileSync('./isrgrootx1.pem')
  }
}) 

Don't need agent.
I don't know how I didn't see this before, sorry.

Now I'm able to use TLS  with my valid certificates on Node 8 with a i386 machine . 
Thank you all.

